and%20other%20labor%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20office%20of%20Attorney%20General%20Andrea%20Joy%20Campbell%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esaid%20this%20week%20that%20it%20issued%20more%20than%20%242%20million%20in%20citations%20against%20Northeast%20Foods%20LLC%2C%20which%20operates%20dozens%20of%20Burger%20King%20franchises%20across%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20fine%20includes%20penalties%20against%20the%20company%20as%20well%20as%20restitution%20for%20unpaid%20wages%2C%20the%20AG's%20office%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECampbell's%20office%20alleged%20that%20the%20franchise%20operator%20assigned%20minors%20to%20work%20outside%20of%20legally%20permitted%20hours%20and%20more%20than%20the%20nine-hour%20daily%20limit%20that%2016%20and%2017%20year%20olds%20can%20work%20under%20state%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AG%20also%20accused%20Northeast%20Foods%20of%20failing%20to%20pay%20workers%20on%20time%2C%20pay%20minimum%20wage%2C%20or%20pay%20workers%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AG's%20office%20said%20it%20launched%20an%20investigation%20into%20the%20matter%20after%20receiving%20a%20complaint%20from%20a%20worker%20at%20a%20Burger%20King%20location%20over%20a%20nonpayment%20of%20wages.%20The%20investigation%20revealed%20that%20nearly%202%2C000%20employees%20at%20Burger%20King%20locations%20operated%20by%20Northeast%20Foods%20across%20Massachusetts%20were%20impacted%20by%20the%20alleged%20violations%2C%20the%20AG's%20office%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20Northeast%20Foods%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBurger%20King's%20press%20representative%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20the%20company%20%26quot%3Bcontacted%20the%20Franchisee%20facing%20these%20violations%20immediately%20upon%20learning%20of%20them%2C%20and%20they%20have%20informed%20us%20they%20are%20looking%20into%20the%20findings%20of%20the%20investigation%2C%20have%20implemented%20measures%20such%20as%20re-training%20their%20management%20teams%20related%20to%20the%20work%20hours%20of%20minors%20and%20putting%20ongoing%20audits%20in%20place%2C%20and%20are%20working%20on%20additional%20actions%20based%20on%20the%20investigation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Campbell's%20office%20said%20in%20the%20same%20press%20release%20that%20it%20reached%20a%20settlement%20with%20two%20owners%20of%2019%20Popeyes%20locations%20across%20Massachusetts.%20As%20part%20of%20that%20settlement%2C%20the%20AG's%20office%20issued%20%24212%2C516%20in%20citations%20against%20the%20operators%2C%20which%20included%20restitution%20for%20impacted%20workers%20and%20penalties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AG's%20office%20said%20the%20New%20Jersey-based%20franchise%20operators%20scheduled%20minors%20for%20work%20during%20prohibited%20hours%20and%20had%20them%20work%20beyond%20the%20daily%20and%20weekly%20hour%20limits.%20They%20also%20didn't%20allow%20some%20workers%20to%20use%20their%20accrued%20sick%20time%2C%20the%20AG's%20office%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20franchise%20operators%20could%20not%20be%20immediately%20reached%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPopeyes'%20corporate%20representatives%20said%20the%20franchisee%20%26quot%3Bfully%20cooperated%20in%20the%20investigation%26quot%3B%20and%20has%20since%20retrained%20its%20team%20and%20is%20enforcing%20a%20payroll%20system%20that%20will%20alert%20team%20members%20when%20it%20is%20time%20to%20clock%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20United%20States%20has%20seen%20an%20increase%20in%20child%20labor%20violations%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20federal%20fiscal%20year%202023%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Labor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.dol.gov%2F2023%2F10%2F19%2Fwage-and-hour-division-working-to-keep-kids-safe%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20nearly%205%2C800%20kids%20employed%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20law%2C%20which%20the%20agency%20said%20was%20an%2088%2