.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-prompt-ai-tell-me-something-about-myself-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20creator%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhistory-of-openai-company-chatgpt-elon-musk-founded-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20intentionally%20ripping%20off%20their%20copyrighted%20content%20to%20train%20its%20large%20language%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMedia%20companies%20Torstar%2C%20Postmedia%2C%20The%20Globe%20and%20Mail%2C%20The%20Canadian%20Press%2C%20and%20CBC%2FRadio-Canada%20allege%20in%20a%20new%20lawsuit%20against%20OpenAI%20that%20the%20artificial%20intelligence%20startup%20has%20%26quot%3Bengaged%20in%20ongoing%2C%20deliberate%2C%20and%20unauthorized%20misappropriation%26quot%3B%20of%20their%20news%20works.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%2C%20filed%20on%20Friday%20in%20the%20Ontario%20Superior%20Court%20of%20Justice%20and%20viewed%20by%20Business%20Insider%2C%20accuses%20OpenAI%20of%20violating%20Canadian%20copyright%20laws%20and%20%26quot%3Bunjustly%20enriching%26quot%3B%20itself%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20news%20media%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20an%20OpenAI%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20its%20models%20are%20%26quot%3Btrained%20on%20publicly%20available%20data%2C%20grounded%20in%20fair%20use%20and%20related%20international%20copyright%20principles%20that%20are%20fair%20for%20creators%20and%20support%20innovation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20collaborate%20closely%20with%20news%20publishers%2C%20including%20in%20the%20display%2C%20attribution%20and%20links%20to%20their%20content%20in%20ChatGPT%20search%2C%20and%20offer%20them%20easy%20ways%20to%20opt-out%20should%20they%20so%20desire%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20news%20companies%20alleged%20in%20a%20joint%20statement%20that%20OpenAI%20%26quot%3Bregularly%20breaches%20copyright%20and%20online%20terms%20of%20use%20by%20scraping%20large%20swaths%20of%20content%20from%20Canadian%20media%20to%20help%20develop%20its%20products%2C%20such%20as%20ChatGPT.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOpenAI%20is%20capitalizing%20and%20profiting%20from%20the%20use%20of%20this%20content%2C%20without%20getting%20permission%20or%20compensating%20content%20owners%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20said.%20%26quot%3BJournalism%20is%20in%20the%20public%20interest.%20OpenAI%20using%20other%20companies'%20journalism%20for%20their%20own%20commercial%20gain%20is%20not.%20It's%20illegal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2084-page%20lawsuit%20seeks%20an%20undisclosed%20amount%20of%20damages%20to%20compensate%20the%20media%20companies%20for%20the%20%26quot%3Bwrongful%20misappropriation%26quot%3B%20of%20their%20works%20as%20well%20as%20a%20permanent%20injunction%20in%20order%20to%20prevent%20OpenAI%20from%20carrying%20out%20%26quot%3Bunlawful%20conduct.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRather%20than%20seek%20to%20obtain%20the%20information%20legally%2C%20OpenAI%20has%20elected%20to%20brazenly%20misappropriate%20the%20News%20Media%20Companies'%20valuable%20intellectual%20property%20and%20convert%20it%20for%20its%20own%20uses%2C%20including%20commercial%20uses%2C%20without%20consent%20or%20consideration%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20alleges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20follows%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-copyright-lawsuit-authors-chatgpt-trained-on-books-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eflurry%20of%20other%20lawsuits%3C%2Fa%3E%20previously%20filed%20by%20authors%2C%20visual%20artists%2C%20news%20outlets%2C%20and%20computer%20coders%20against%20AI%20companies%20like%20OpenAI%2C%20arguing%20that%20their%20original%20works%20were%20used%20to%20train%20AI%20tools%20without%20their%20permission.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EOther%20media%20organizations%2C%20including%20Axel%20Springer%2C%20the%20parent%20company%20of%20Busine