20on%20the%20automotive%20industry%2C%20where%20high-grade%20plastic%20is%20used%20for%20manufacturing%20car%20parts.%20%E2%80%98Dump%20In%20Bin%E2%80%99%20began%20processing%20plastic%20waste%20from%20automotive%20manufacturers%2C%20refining%20their%20segregation%20process%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20plastics%20were%20sorted%20properly%20before%20being%20recycled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrough%20a%20thorough%20and%20diligent%20process%2C%20the%20company%20built%20expertise%20in%20plastic%20recycling%2C%20particularly%20in%20turning%20plastic%20waste%20into%20usable%20raw%20materials.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20initial%20trails%20were%20maddening!%20We%20even%20built%20small%20%3Cem%3Echulas%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20experimented%20with%20melting%20small%20amounts%20of%20plastic%20in%20pans%2C%20using%20different%20methods%20at%20a%20very%20small%20scale%20to%20see%20what%20works%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Nitin.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201280px)%20100vw%2C%201280px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-11-19-at-3.31.54-PM-1732198155.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%20'Plave%2C'%20a%20precast%20concrete%20material%20created%20from%20recycled%20demolition%20debris%20and%20plastic%20waste.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-11-19-at-3.31.54-PM-1732198155.jpeg%201280w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-11-19-at-3.31.54-PM-1732198155-300x169.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-11-19-at-3.31.54-PM-1732198155-500x281.jpeg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-11-19-at-3.31.54-PM-1732198155-768x432.jpeg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-11-19-at-3.31.54-PM-1732198155-1200x675.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-11-19-at-3.31.54-PM-1732198155-150x84.jpeg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-381947%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EPLAVE%20(a%20play%20on%20the%20words%20%E2%80%98pavement%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98plastic%E2%80%99)%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20they%20help%20small%20and%20medium-sized%20manufacturing%20companies%20(SMEs)%20to%20make%20a%20more%20sustainable%20and%20cheaper%20choice%20in%20their%20production%20process.%20%E2%80%9CRecycled%20plastic%20can%20be%20used%20for%20anything%2C%20but%20we%20make%20sure%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20used%20for%20or%20around%20food%20packaging.%20Because%20it%E2%80%99s%20still%20plastic%2C%20recycled%20or%20not%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Rishabh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%5Cn%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20focus%20on%20sustainability%20has%20paid%20off.%20%E2%80%98Dump%20In%20Bin%E2%80%99%20has%20recycled%20over%2048%20lakh%20kg%20of%20plastic%2C%20bringing%20in%20a%20revenue%20of%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20every%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EPLAVE%3A%20A%20breakthrough%20in%20sustainability%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20founders%20had%20bigger%20aspirations.%20They%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20be%20just%20another%20recycling%20company%3B%20they%20wanted%20to%20solve%20the%20problem%20of%20waste%20in%20a%20more%20tangible%20and%20sustainable%20way.%20The%20idea%20of%20creating%20a%20product%20that%20could%20replace%20cement%2C%20one%20of%20the%20most%20carbon-intensive%20materials%20used%20in%20construction%2C%20became%20their%20next%20goal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weforum.org%2Fstories%2F2024%2F09%2Fcement-production-sustainable-concrete-co2-emissions%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWorld%20Economic%20Forum%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20global%20cement%20manufacturing%20produced%201.6%20billion%20metric%20tonnes%20of%20CO2%20in%202022%20alone%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20about%208%25%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20total%20CO2%20emissions%2C%20making%20it%20a%20significant%20contributor%20to%20climate%20change.%20The%20challenge%20was%20daunting%3A%20they%20needed%20to%20find%20a%20way%20to%20make%20a%20product%20that%20could%20replace%20cement%20but%20still%20meet%20the%20high-quality%20standards%20required%20for%20construction%20materials.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20breakthrough%20came%20when%20they%20stumbled%20upon%20a%20decade-old%20research%20project%20that%20explored%20mixing%20plastic%20with%20sand%20to%20create%20concrete.%20However%2C%20the%20research%20was%20still%20in%20its%20infancy%2C%20and%20the%20existing%20products%20didn%E2%80%99t%20match%20the%20quality%20of%20cement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20nearly%20two%20years%20of%20research%20and%20development%2C%20they%20created%20PLAVE%20(a%20play%20on%20the%20words%20%E2%80%98pavement%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98plastic%E2%80%99)%20%E2%80%94%20a%20unique%20construction%20material%20made%20from%20a%20blend%20of%20plastic%20waste%20and%20demolition%20debris.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201280px)%20100vw%2C%201280px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FIMG_20241119_172305_7303-3-1732198244.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rishabh%20Patel%20and%20Nitin%20Yadav%20in%20their%20plastic%20recycling%20facility.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FIMG_20241119_172305_7303-3-1732198244.jpg%201280w%2C%20https%3